this endpoint retrieves sets an object's image or retrieves its image's url . 
where you have to send the object's id and the image type and image - image is not obligation for POST request -. as following :

	{
		"id" : <integer> ,
		'type' , # values are provided above ,
		'image' : <image_file>
	}
the supported image types are :

	"profile" =>  this arg represents the user-profile's image ,
	"car" 		=> this arg represents the user-car's image 
response Ex on the GET reuqets :

	{
			"url": 
		"http://127.0.0.1:8000/media/images/users/thumbnails/Developper_01__Converted__generated_jFWw6Bk.jpg"
	}

response Ex on the POST request :

	{
		'success' : 'image has been uploaded successfully'
	}

